<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF46FF0CA7ADFC39FD6CD96B" pageId="223" pageNumber="224" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF46FF0CA7ADFC39FEF0DFF1" blockId="223.[189,310,982,1008]" box="[189,310,982,1008]" pageId="223" pageNumber="224">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF46FF0CA7ADFC39FEF0DFF1" bold="true" box="[189,310,982,1008]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="223" pageNumber="224" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF46FF0CA7ADFC39FEF0DFF1" bold="true" box="[189,310,982,1008]" pageId="223" pageNumber="224">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF46FF0CA7ADFBE8FC02D86A" blockId="223.[189,1400,1031,1132]" pageId="223" pageNumber="224">
This species may be separated from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF46FF0CA427FBE8FCBDD820" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[823,891,1031,1057]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Sarax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="223" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF46FF0CA427FBE8FCBDD820" box="[823,891,1031,1057]" italics="true" pageId="223" pageNumber="224">Sarax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Africa, the Middle East and South Asia by the following combination of characters: 6–8 anterior setae on carapace; median eyes extremely reduced; median ocular tubercle absent; lateral eyes very reduced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF46FF0CA7ADFB79FD6CD96B" blockId="223.[187,1399,1173,1386]" pageId="223" pageNumber="224">
It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF46FF0CA67DFB7AFDC8D8AE" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[365,526,1173,1199]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="223" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ioanniticus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF46FF0CA67DFB7AFDC8D8AE" box="[365,526,1173,1199]" italics="true" pageId="223" pageNumber="224">S. ioanniticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2EADC30AFF46FF0CA507FB7AFD5DD8B1" box="[535,667,1173,1200]" pageId="223" pageNumber="224" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
as follows: reduction of the median and lateral eyes; number of spines on the pedipalp, the femur with four dorsal spines and four ventral spines in 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF46FF0CA3C9FB54FAB0D8D5" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[1241,1398,1210,1237]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="223" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="israelensis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF46FF0CA3C9FB54FAB0D8D5" box="[1241,1398,1210,1237]" italics="true" pageId="223" pageNumber="224">S. israelensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2EADC30AFF46FF0CA7ADFB30FEF9D8FB" box="[189,319,1247,1274]" pageId="223" pageNumber="224" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
compared with five dorsal spines and five ventral spines in 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF46FF0CA4ECFB0FFB5DD8F8" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[1020,1179,1248,1274]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="223" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ioanniticus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF46FF0CA4ECFB0FFB5DD8F8" box="[1020,1179,1248,1274]" italics="true" pageId="223" pageNumber="224">S. ioanniticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
