<paragraph id="0755A263FF79FF33A7ADFE41FC16DDC9" blockId="224.[189,976,430,457]" box="[189,976,430,457]" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">This troglobitic species is restricted to a cave in a semi-arid region.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF79FF33A7ADFE1DFDEFDEFB" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF79FF33A7ADFE1DFEE9DE0D" blockId="224.[189,303,498,524]" box="[189,303,498,524]" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF79FF33A7ADFE1DFEE9DE0D" bold="true" box="[189,303,498,524]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF79FF33A7ADFE1DFEE9DE0D" bold="true" box="[189,303,498,524]" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF79FF33A7ADFDCCFDEFDEFB" blockId="224.[189,1399,547,762]" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">
This species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF79FF33A54BFDCBFD39DE3C" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[603,767,548,574]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ioanniticus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF79FF33A54BFDCBFD39DE3C" box="[603,767,548,574]" italics="true" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">S. ioanniticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2EADC30AFF79FF33A41CFDCCFC53DE3F" box="[780,917,547,574]" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, which overlaps its distribution. It was originally described in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF79FF33A550FDA6FD6BDE62" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" box="[576,685,585,611]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF79FF33A550FDA6FD6BDE62" box="[576,685,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">Charinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is hereby transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF79FF33A4EBFDA6FBF9DE62" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[1019,1087,585,611]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Sarax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF79FF33A4EBFDA6FBF9DE62" box="[1019,1087,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">Sarax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the phylogenetic analyses of 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF79FF33A65DFD81FD92DE88" author="Miranda G. S. &amp; Giupponi A. P. &amp; Scharff N. &amp; Prendini L." box="[333,596,622,649]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Miranda" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" refId="ref151478" refString="Miranda G. S., Giupponi A. P., Scharff N. &amp; Prendini L. 2021. Phylogeny and biogeography of the pantropical whip spider family Charinidae (Arachnida: Amblypygi). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zlaa 101" title="Phylogeny and biogeography of the pantropical whip spider family Charinidae (Arachnida: Amblypygi)" type="book" year="2021">
<collectingRegion id="C52E6C81FF79FF33A65DFD81FE76DE89" box="[333,432,622,648]" country="Venezuela" name="Miranda" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">Miranda</collectingRegion>
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF79FF33A6ABFD80FE3EDE89" box="[443,504,622,648]" italics="true" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">et al.</emphasis>
(2021)
</bibRefCitation>
. The morphological characters that support its placement in 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF79FF33A222FD80FAB0DE88" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[1330,1398,623,649]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Sarax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF79FF33A222FD80FAB0DE88" box="[1330,1398,623,649]" italics="true" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">Sarax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
include the lateral eyes situated near the lateral margin of the carapace, the presence of a seta lateral to the lateral ocular triad, and the finger-like female gonopod. See 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF79FF33A4BDFD55FB73DED4" author="Miranda G. S. &amp; Aharon S. &amp; Gavish-Regev E. &amp; Giupponi A. P. L. &amp; Wizen G." box="[941,1205,698,725]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Miranda" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" pagination="1 - 17" part="234" refId="ref151133" refString="Miranda G. S., Aharon S., Gavish-Regev E., Giupponi A. P. L. &amp; Wizen G. 2016 a. A new species of Charinus Simon, 1892 (Arachnida: Amblypygi: Charinidae) from Israel and new records of C. ioanniticus (Kritscher, 1959). European Journal of Taxonomy 234: 1 - 17. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2016.234" title="A new species of Charinus Simon, 1892 (Arachnida: Amblypygi: Charinidae) from Israel and new records of C. ioanniticus (Kritscher, 1959)" type="journal article" year="2016" yearSuffix="a">
<collectingRegion id="C52E6C81FF79FF33A4BDFD55FBD6DED5" box="[941,1040,698,724]" country="Venezuela" name="Miranda" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">Miranda</collectingRegion>
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF79FF33A307FD54FB94DED5" box="[1047,1106,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">et al.</emphasis>
(2016a)
</bibRefCitation>
for more details about 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF79FF33A615FD0FFE66DEF8" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[261,416,735,762]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="israelensis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF79FF33A615FD0FFE66DEF8" box="[261,416,735,762]" italics="true" pageId="224" pageNumber="225">S. israelensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2EADC30AFF79FF33A6B8FD30FDEFDEFB" box="[424,553,735,762]" pageId="224" pageNumber="225" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
